  <h1>Privacy Policy – Abdou Bot</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> April 25, 2025</p>

  <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Abdou Bot</strong> collects, uses, and protects your data when you use the bot.</p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>User Data</strong>: Abdou Bot may collect user IDs, messages, and moderation logs to perform bot functions.</li>
    <li><strong>Anonymous Data</strong>: We do not store personal information unless explicitly provided by users for creating fake identities or sending anonymous messages.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Moderation</strong>: User data may be logged for moderation purposes, such as kicks, bans, timeouts, and untimeouts.</li>
    <li><strong>Anonymous Features</strong>: Data such as fake identities and messages may be stored temporarily for the purposes of delivering the service.</li>
    <li><strong>Bot Functionality</strong>: We collect data for improving the bot's functions, including auto-reactions and replies.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Data Storage & Protection</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Storage</strong>: Data may be temporarily stored to fulfill specific bot functions. We will delete data as requested or automatically after a defined period.</li>
    <li><strong>Security</strong>: We take reasonable precautions to protect the data you share with Abdou Bot.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>Abdou Bot does not share user data with third parties, except for Discord's own API for necessary bot functions.</p>

  <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>You may request to delete your data, including messages, fake identities, and logs, by contacting the bot’s admin or through available commands.</p>

  <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy from time to time. Continued use of Abdou Bot after updates signifies your acceptance of the new terms.</p>
</body>
